            <pb n="1"/>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee> in <placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cleveland&#44;</placeName>
                <date>August 1st 5612</date> AM</p>
            <p>Dear sir&#58;</p>

            <p rend="indent(1)">This is to inform you that I am now able<lb/> to send you within 14 days the
                continuation&#44; that is<lb/> the entire manuscript of my work which I<lb/> intend
                to publish. <del>Should</del> it<add>&#63;</add> would make me very happy if you not yet have
                    chang<add>ed</add><lb/> your decision&#44; as you told me in your recent
                    lette<add>r</add><lb/> and started with my work. But should that not<lb/> be the
                case&#44; I ask you&#44; to send me the manusc<add>ript</add><lb/> as soon as
                possible by express. I shall be glad to<lb/> pay for the postage. I suppose that you
                have<lb/> printed <del>my es</del> already my essays&#44; concerning the<lb/> G E T in the
                Occident. In case you have<lb/> failed to print them&#44; may I ask you to have
                    the<add>m</add><lb/> printed in the very next issue. I <sic>dont</sic> doubt for
                a<lb/> moment &#40;note his psychology&#41; that you will gra<add>nt</add><lb/> me
                as much right and justice as you gran<add>t</add><lb/>
                <persName>Levi</persName>. You can see&#44; that in my essays I<lb/> did not <del>mak</del>
                mention any <del>personalities</del> pers<add>&#63;</add><lb/> though I possess ample material
                &#40;note psycholo<add>&#63;</add><lb/> I only discussed in detail the
                questionable<lb/> object itself. Although I <del>still</del> would have to<lb/> say still a
                whole lot in this respect&#44;</p>

            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>however&#44; I think that the matter is by far<lb/> finished&#44; and a remark made
                at the proper time weig<add>&#63;</add><lb/> more&#44; than rash untimely
                expressions. As a fighter f<add>or</add><lb/> Jewish truths you&#44; as an editor
                really shoul<add>d</add><lb/> not belong to any party but should permit<lb/> anybody
                to step in the arena &#40;to show his wits&#41;<lb/> so that the literary &#40;the
                German orthography&#44; used by<lb/><persName>Kalisch</persName> is wrong&#44;
                considering the time in which it<lb/> was written. He writes according to sound not
                acco<lb/> to rules&#41; public may and can pass a correct<lb/> sentence and the
                truth may really be found<lb/> out. Whatever more I would have to say
                <add>on</add><lb/> this subject you will find if you think (contem/plate) at bit for
                yourself&#44; and so I <del>finish</del> end my let<add>ter</add><lb/> hoping that you will
                fulfill my desires as<lb/> I expressed them in this letter. Ex&#8212;<lb/>pecting
                your early reply&#44; I am<lb/> Very truly yours<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Isidor Kalisch</persName></p>

        </body>
